  "texts": [
    "It would also be desirable to explore intra-and interphysician variation in the generation of answers under multiple scenarios as well as contextualize LLM performance by comparison to the range of approaches that might be expected among physicians.",
    "Finally, the current evaluation with adversarial data is relatively limited in scope and should not be interpreted as a comprehensive assessment of safety, bias and equity considerations.",
    "In future work, adversarial data could be systematically expanded to increase coverage of health equity topics and facilitate disaggregated evaluation over sensitive characteristics [43] [44] [45].",
    "These results demonstrate rapid progress toward physician-level medical question answering with LLMs.",
    "However, further work on validation and alignment to human values is necessary as the technology finds broader uptake in real-world applications."
